per place to associate a policy with a user is at the user level.\r\n\r\nI assumed that I would be able to associate a policy at the account level, and that adding a policy there would cascade down to all users.  But when I tried to add a policy under the \"account\" screen, I received an error: \r\n\"Failed to add policy Allow-all: Failed to add policy Allow-all to account 073501631485: Access to the resource is denied\".\r\n\r\nIt's unclear why there's a button to allow \"Add policy\" at the accounts level -- it's confusing to have the button here if it doesn't work.\r\n\r\nSee EUCA-2233 for additional discussion, and another instance where this caught users unawares.","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":"PRD-36","customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Admin UI: \"Add Policy\" button on Accounts screen is unclear","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=gregdek","name":"gregdek","key":"gregdek","accountId":"557058:03f83db3-3217-4d33-ab46-1e156057c13d","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/152ea15ef67a66fe6a55c0ae34273f55?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/152ea15ef67a66fe6a55c0ae34273f55?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/152ea15ef67a66fe6a55c0ae34273f55?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/152ea15ef67a66fe6a55c0ae34273f55?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"display